  <description><![CDATA[<p>It’s hard to decide what we like more about the Hotel Aaritz – the elegant interiors with the comfy sofas that invite you to relax in the lobby or the location, right in front of the Ciampinoi gondola. It couldn’t be easier to head up into the mountains and discover some of the best walking trails in the <a data-udi="umb://document/f7e065ba2a3d40d7893ad1b116880496" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f7e065ba2a3d40d7893ad1b116880496}" title="The Dolomites">Dolomites</a>. Just don’t forget your camera as the views are incredible!</p>
<h2>A relaxing Dolomite retreat</h2>
<p>You’ll be well taken care of at this hotel. There’s a very relaxing atmosphere throughout, helped by the warm colours in the lobby and rooms. They’ve all got private balconies that are nice place to relax before dinner. Or you can head to the bar and try a glass of local wine.</p>
<h2>Inviting spa facilities</h2>
<p>There’s so much to see and do around the area but if you do find yourself with a bit of spare time, we recommend heading to the spa. There’s a lovely indoor pool that has access to the garden so you can top up your tan. There’s a Turkish bath, sauna and fully-equipped gym too. If you fancy spoiling yourself, book in for a treatment. It’s the perfect way to get those legs ready for some more mountain trails the next day.</p>]]></description>
